	<div id="congratsTxt" class="txtFrame">
		<div class="txtCenter">
			<h1>Well Done!</h1>
			<p style="margin-bottom: 30px;">You&#8217;ve done a great job of figuring out what the artist Hiram Powers was up to. <a href="http://americanart.si.edu/collections/search/artwork/?id=20136"><font color="#FFFFFF"><u>Psyche</u></font></a> was a mortal girl who became immortal&#8212;like a caterpillar becoming a butterfly. The artist placed a butterfly in her hair. <a href="http://americanart.si.edu/collections/search/artwork/?id=20026"><font color="#FFFFFF"><u>Clytie</u></font></a> became a sunflower. The artist gave her sunflower petals. <a href="http://americanart.si.edu/collections/search/artwork/?id=20032"><font color="#FFFFFF"><u>Artemis</u></font></a> was the goddess of the moon. The artist gave her a crescent moon. He also represented her modesty with a toga, which Psyche and Clytie do not have.</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 30px;">Now use your symbol-sleuthing skills in <a href="/idealabs/myths/symbolsinastory/"><font color="#FFFFFF"><u>Symbols in a Story</u></font></a>.</p>
			<p><a href="#" id="replayBtn" class="readyBtn">Replay?</a></p>
		</div>
